9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 784, L.D. 1179, “An Act to Establish
10 Minimum Safety Standards for the Construction and Use of Temporary Emergency
11 Shelters”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2452, first ¶, as repealed and replaced by PL 2011, c. 691, Pt.
15 A, §25, is amended to read:
16 The Commissioner of Public Safety shall adopt and may amend rules governing the
17 safety to life from fire in or around all buildings or other structures, recreational vehicles
18 as defined in National Fire Protection Association standard 1192 and mass outdoor
19 gatherings, as defined in Title 22, section 1601, subsection 2, within the commissioner's
20 jurisdiction. Automatic sprinkler systems may not be required in existing noncommercial
21 places of assembly. Noncommercial places of assembly include those facilities used for
22 such purposes as deliberation, worship, entertainment, amusement or awaiting
23 transportation that have a capacity of 100 to 300 persons. Automatic sprinkler systems
24 may not be required in existing commercial places of assembly that are open for no more
25 than 50 days per calendar year. "Commercial places of assembly" includes bars with live
26 entertainment, dance halls, nightclubs, assembly halls with large open areas in which
27 patrons stand or sit, commonly referred to as "festival seating," and restaurants. Rules
28 adopted pursuant to this section are routine technical rules, except that rules pertaining to
29 fire sprinklers are major substantive rules, both of which are defined in Title 5, chapter 375,
30 subchapter 2‑A.
31 Sec. 2. 25 MRSA §2452, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2003, c. 535, §3, is further
32 amended to read:
33 3. Violation. A person who violates a rule issued by the commissioner under this
34 section commits a Class E crime. Violation of this section is a strict liability crime as
35 defined in Title 17-A, section 34, subsection 4-A.
