COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 784, L.D. 1179
1 Sec. 3. Report. The Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal,
2 shall notify the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing
3 matters if the department proposes to adopt through rulemaking the National Fire
4 Protection Association standard 1192 on recreational vehicles.'
5 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
6 number to read consecutively.
7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment directs the Commissioner of Public
99 Safety to adopt rules governing the safety to life from fire in or around recreational vehicles
1100 as defined in National Fire Protection Association standard 1192 and stipulates that a
1111 violation of a rule adopted pursuant to the requirement is a strict liability crime as defined
1122 in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 17-A, section 34, subsection 4-A. The amendment also
1133 requires the Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal to notify the
1144 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters if the
1155 department proposes to adopt through rulemaking the National Fire Protection Association
1166 standard 1192.
1177 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
